Description: Body sherd of East Greek grey ware pottery closed vessel, possibly an amphora; grooved decoration consisting of part of two petals of a circumscribed palmette; dark grey fabric with mica and limestone inclusions; very worn dark grey slip on exterior.
Curator's comments: Sherd probably belongs to the same vessel as British Museum 1924,1201.61 and 1924,1201.63.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.006)
